<p>I am developing an Android app using Ionic and the <a href="http://ngcordova.com/docs/plugins/fileTransfer/" rel="nofollow">ngCordova File Transfer plugin</a> to upload files to Amazon S3. However, uploaded files appear to have extra content, like <code>Content-Disposition...</code> as seen below: </p>  <pre><code>--+++++ Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="IMG_20150817_205738_1439818078787.jpg" Content-Type: image/jpeg &lt;ORIGINAL FILE CONTENT GOES HERE&gt; --+++++-- </code></pre>  <p>My code is as follows:</p>  <pre><code>$cordovaFileTransfer.upload(signedPutUrl, fileUrl, {     fileKey: "file",     fileName: fileName,     mimeType: 'image/jpeg',     chunkedMode: false,     httpMethod: 'PUT',     encodeURI: false,     params: {         "Content-Type": "application/octet-stream"     } }, true) </code></pre>  <p>Why is this the case and how can I avoid this?</p>